article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 78, Tennessee St. 65
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. -- Lester Hudson scored 30 points to lead Tennessee-Martin to a 78-65 win over in-state foe Tennessee State on Saturday night. Marquis Weddle added 23 points and Olajide Hay had 15 for the Skyhawks (9-6, 2-3 Ohio Valley Conference), who trailed by a point at halftime before outscoring the Tigers 52-39 in the second half to seal the win. Gerald Robinson Jr. led the Tigers (5-11, 3-3) with 14 points and Darius Cox added 10. The Skyhawks hit 22-of-30 free throws in the game compared to the Tigers, who went just 7-for-15 from the line. Both teams had rough night from beyond the arc, as the Skyhawks went 10 of 21, compared to a 4 of 11 mark for the Tigers. Tennessee State did outrebound Tennessee-Martin 41-32.
